title: Sex Kittens Go To College Extended International Version (1960)
description:
Sex Kittens Go To College (Extended International Version) 1960
directed and produced by Albert Zugsmith

Runtime 103 minutes

IMDb  tt0054298

Mamie Van Doren
Tuesday Weld
Mijanou Bardot
Mickey Shaughnessy
Martin (Route 66) Milner
Vampira
Jackie (Uncle Fester) Coogan

... and many more of the studio players familiar to film and television
audiences of the period.  (Tuesday Weld was featured on Dobie Gillis which is 
currently being shared here in  easy to grab single episodes.)


Summary

   "'Sex Kitten, American Version' Mamie van Doren joins forces with 'Sex 
Kitten, junior grade' Tuesday Weld and 'Sex Kitten, French version' Mijanou 
Bardot for this screwball campus comedy that prefigures both grind house flicks 
and family-friendly college capers. When Collins College digital supercomputer, 
Thinko picks Dr. Mathilda West to head their science department, nobody expects 
the polymath savant to pack more curves than a rack full of test tubes. While 
the faculty struggles to pick their slack jaws up off the floor, a crew of 
gangsters puts the muscle on the 'bot, thanks to Thinko's knack for picking the 
ponies".

My notes

   The film (made available in 2013) is not elsewhere on the file shares that I 
know of.   And the "extended version" contains footage that is risque but not 
with any  anatomy you haven't seen on "Game Of Thrones".  SKGtC has a Wiki and 
more about the extended 'international' version is contained there.  Also in 
this regard it's interesting to note that "Marty" Milner was a producer on the 
show.

  SKGtC may be considered camp or ripe for sarcastic remarks as dated and 
'naive' or even in questionable taste.  It is, I think, a good representative 
period piece of gags and humor.   

  Of note is that for some reason "Collins College" appears more than once in 
these films of the period.  "College Confidential" with Steve Allen (yes _the_ 
Steve Allen) also uses the name. 

  This is another in the collection of Mamie Van Doren films.  When "Girls 
Town" becomes available  it will appear as well.


Notes written  May 22nd,   2015
